! conclusion: Use the pattern-action RPC to log read/update/implement actions during the run.
  + context: MUSN expects structured pattern action logs to support PSR/PUR checks.
  + IF:
    Pattern actions are only described in free text or skipped.
  + HOWEVER:
    The agent may still need freedom to work in the repo.
  + THEN:
    Log each pattern action via RPC with an explicit action and note.
  + BECAUSE:
    Structured action logs keep evidence coherent and machine-checkable.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: turn/action events with :pattern/id, :action, and :note.
    - evidence-shape: {:pattern/id :string, :action :string, :note :string}
